    "Reason : 1 - The proposed hip-to-gable roof extension, rear dormer and roof windows, by reason of their position, size, height, design and appearance, would be an intrusive, incongruous and inappropriate development in Wellesley Road Conservation Area, unbalancing this row of terrace houses, failing to maintain and enhance the appearance and character of the street and the wider Conservation Area, contrary to Hounslow Character, Sustainability and Design SPD, Local Plan policies CC1; CC2; CC4; SC7, and the intent of the National Planning Policy Framework.",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed extensions, by reason of no valid fire safety information submitted, fails to ensure the safety of all building users, contrary to London Plan policy D12 and the intent of the National Planning Policy Framework."
